Koha REST server
================

Installation notes:
-------------------

A/ If you have a tarball

Simply extract files into Koha installation directory:

    cd /path/to/koha
    tar xzf koha-restful.tar.gz


B/ If you want to install it as a git repository

If Koha installation directory is not a git repository, you can just clone Koha
REST server into it:

    cd /path/to/koha
    git clone git://git.biblibre.com/koha-restful.git .

Otherwise (Koha installation directory is a git repository), you have to clone
koha REST server in another location and then symlink files and directories into
Koha installation directory:

    ln -s /path/to/koharest/etc/rest /path/to/koha/etc/
    ln -s /path/to/koharest/Koha/REST /path/to/koha/Koha/
    ln -s /path/to/koharest/opac/rest.pl /path/to/koha/opac/

Important note: '/path/to/koharest' must be absolute path when creating symlink.
